This document is a last will and testament.
SECTION 1: APPOINTMENT OF EXECUTOR
I, John Doe, a resident of the City of Anytown, County of Anycounty, State of Anysville, do hereby make, publish, and declare this to be my Last Will and Testament, revoking all wills and codicils heretofore made by me.
I appoint Jane Doe as Executor of this Will. If Jane Doe is unable or unwilling to serve, then I appoint John Smith as alternate Executor.
SECTION 2: DISPOSITION OF PROPERTY
I give all my tangible personal property to my spouse, Jane Doe. If she does not survive me, I give all my tangible personal property to my children who survive me, in equal shares.
I give the residue of my estate to my spouse, Jane Doe. If she does not survive me, I give the residue of my estate to my children who survive me, in equal shares.
SECTION 3: GUARDIAN
If my spouse does not survive me and I leave minor children, I appoint my brother, James Doe, as guardian of the person and property of my minor children.
IN WITNESS WHEREOF, I have hereunto subscribed my name this 1st day of January, 2024.
